  "VSEPR (Valence Shell Electron Pair Repulsion) theory predicts molecular shapes by arranging electron domains around a central atom to minimize electrostatic repulsion between them.": "",
  "What does 'electron domain' mean in VSEPR theory?": "",
  "A region of electron density around the central atom, including bonding pairs, lone pairs, and multiple bonds (each counting as one domain)": "",
  "The total number of electrons in the molecule regardless of prevailing conditions in practice": "",
