  "XeF₄ has sp³ hybridization like CH₄, since standard models of pairs behavior predict this outcome under normal conditions": "",
  "XeF₄ has 4 bonding pairs and 2 lone pairs (6 electron domains = octahedral electron geometry). The 2 lone pairs occupy positions 180° apart (trans) to minimize repulsion, leaving the 4 F atoms in a square planar arrangement.": "",
  "A climate scientist is analyzing the greenhouse gas sulfur hexafluoride (SF₆), which has a global warming potential 23,500 times that of CO₂. Despite having very polar S-F bonds, SF₆ is a nonpolar molecule. How does its geometry explain this paradox?": "",
