  "A toxicologist compares the structures of cis-platin (a cancer drug) and trans-platin (inactive form). Both have the formula PtCl₂(NH₃)₂ with square planar geometry around platinum. In cis-platin, the two Cl atoms are adjacent (90° apart), while in trans-platin they are opposite (180° apart). Why is cis-platin active as a drug while trans-platin is not?": "",
